<h2 id="how-to-practice-these">How to practice these</h2>

<p>First, understand these foundational chord positions weâ€™ll be using. 5th and 6th strings only for all three chords. For the G and the A, use your left index finger to barre the 5th and 6th strings on either the 5th fret (for the G chord) or the 7th fret (for the A) chord. See my video lesson for a demonstration.</p>

