<p>Next, the idea is to add a single note on top of the existing chord positions you know â€“ and to get comfortable going back &amp; forth between the main chord position, and the with-added-note chord position. For the D, youâ€™ll want to add a single finger on the 2nd fret of the 5th fret (left index is fine). For the G and the A, youâ€™ll want to use your left ring finger to play the additional note â€“ while your left index is barring the 5th or 7th fret. Again, see my video lesson for a demonstration.</p>

